<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn272">  272  Shaun's attitude to Shem is unchanged from I.6, where he disavows any responsibility for his brother's welfare, while at the same time professing that he cares for him. His ambiguity is succinctly stated at 317.15 (408.18): &lsquo;I'm an everdevoting fiend of his.&rsquo;  </div>
